=== Festival ===
; {{ill|lt=regular festival|Q11385469|qid=Q11385469|1=Reisai}}
: {{ill|lt=November 1st|Q2997|qid=Q2997|1=November 1}} The most important festival of the year. During the festival, in addition to the ritual of hot water, a shrine maiden dance called ``Hagoromo no Mai'' is dedicated at the Maiden. This hagoromo dance is also dedicated at the autumn festival. <ref name="historical book"/>
; Tsutsugayu festival
: "Tsukayusai". A festival to pray for a good harvest that is held from the night of {{ill|lt=February 14th|Q2332|qid=Q2332|1=February 14}} to {{ill|lt=February 15th|Q2334|qid=Q2334|lt=15th|1=February 15}}. As part of the ritual, first a large cauldron is set up in front of the shrine and preparations are made to boil porridge. Then, in the middle of the night, a shrine is set up on the beach to welcome the gods, and a ceremony is performed by singing prayers without using any bonfires. The welcomed god resides in a Himorogi, and the Shinto priest carries the Himorogi through a row of pine trees to reach the shrine grounds. Afterwards, porridge is boiled in a large pot in front of the shrine, a bamboo tube is placed in it, and the amount of porridge in the tube is used to predict the year's crop. <ref name="Historic Book"/>{{Sfn|Miho Shrine (Gods)|1987}}

=== Cultural assets ===

=== Important cultural property (designated by the country) ===
* Tachi Mumei (attached to Itomaki Tachi Koshirae) (craft)
*: Written by {{ill|lt=Kamakura period|Q236205|qid=Q236205|1=Kamakura period}}. The blade is 95.2 cm long and the curve is 4.2 cm <ref name="Yoshisho"/>. Designated on April 30, 1921 (Taisho 10) <ref>{{Nationally Designated Cultural Properties Database|201|6198|Tachi Mumei}}</ref>.

=== Cultural property designated by Shizuoka City ===
*Tangible cultural property
** Main shrine (2 ridge tags, 1 pair of guardian dogs) (building) - Designated on February 23, 1996 <ref name="city designation">{{PDFlink|[http://www.city.shizuoka.jp/000719631.pdf List of city-designated cultural properties]}} (Shizuoka City homepage). </ref>.
** 2 bamboo blinds (craft) - Designated on November 21, 1988 <ref name="city designation"/>.

=== Others ===
* Rip of Feathers
*: A slit that is said to be a piece of hagoromo that appears in the legend of hagoromo <ref name="history book"/>. It is believed to be a piece of Hire/Momo from over 1,200 years ago, and it is also assumed that it originated from the continent based on the pattern of the textile.
* Hagoromo flute - A flute played during the Hagoromo dance.
* Miho old picture map
* Sanhoshaki

